    <header class="detail__header">
      <h1>About</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="detail__body">
      <p>
        I'm a designer based in Melbourne. Currently leading design on Western Union's
        AU digital wallet — a multicurrency consumer wallet built within a global
        design system that needed to flex.
      </p>

      <p>
        Before this I spent six years at ANZ, where I was one of the principal
        designers on ANZ Plus from concept through to a digital-first bank serving
        millions of Australians. I led the design system effort across iOS, Android,
        web, email, and AEM — the components from that system see over five times the
        usage of their ANZ Classic counterparts.
      </p>

      <p>
        Most of my work lives in financial services. I care about the systems thinking
        and design infrastructure that lets product teams move fast without breaking
        the things that matter. I've been mentoring designers for over a decade — five
        of the people I worked with at ANZ have moved into senior or leadership roles
        during my time there.
      </p>

      <p>
        Outside the day job I run <a href="https://leroice.com">leroice</a> as a
        long-standing creative practice — design system tooling, brand work, and the
        occasional 3D illustration project. It's where I keep practising the
        disciplines product work doesn't always exercise.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
